er in a compact, useful order, while minimizing changes and preserving existing test expectations where appropriate.\\n\\nProposed default format:\\n\\\"%(levelname)-8s %(name)s:%(filename)s:%(lineno)d %(message)s\\\"\\n\\nNotes:\\n- Keep change minimal and confined to the logging configuration.\\n- Update tests that expect the old format, or modify formatting in a way that preserves back-compat where possible.\\n\\nFailing tests observed:\\n- testing/logging/test_reporting.py::test_log_cli_enabled_disabled[True]\\n- testing/logging/test_reporting.py::test_log_cli_default_level\\n- testing/logging/test_reporting.py::test_sections_single_new_line_after_test_outcome\\n\\nPlan:\\n1. Create a small change to update DEFAULT_LOG_FORMAT in the logging module.\\n2. Run tests to see failures.\\n3. Modify or update tests to match the new format where necessary, keeping changes minimal.\\n4. Add changelog entry if needed.\\n\\nTickets:\\n- 001-update-default-log-format: Change DEFAULT_LOG_FORMAT to include %(name)s\\n- 002-update-tests: Update tests that embed expected output to match new format\\n- 003-run-ci-and-fix: Run test suite and iterate on failures\\n\\nAssignees: Engineer for code change, CodeReviewer for review, QA for validation\\n\"}", "name": "board_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to /home/cerberose/mas-evaluate-script/runs/benchmark/mas_decentralized/pytest-dev__pytest-5227/repeat_1/project_board/pytest-5227-improve-log-format/000_issue.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_pjOebleDQssh5ngJqbM4KsQV"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_HN2m2RUPUjc18oyFpxFU808u", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"data/project_board/pytest-5227-improve-log-format/001-update-default-log-format.md\",\"content\":\"Title: 001-update-default-log-format\\n\\nChange: Update DEFAULT_LOG_FORMAT in _pytest/logging.py to include %(name)s\\n\\nTasks:\\n- Locate DEFAULT_LOG_FORMAT definition in _pytest/logging.py\\n